# --- Private household data ---
# Ratings, meal history and household details are personal.
# They are ignored by default so the repository can be shared publicly
# while keeping only the reusable knowledge (recipes/ + ingredients/).
# Remove the line below if you want to version-control your household data
# in a PRIVATE repository.
household/

# --- Generated weekly outputs ---
# Weekly menus are kept in git as a nice history of what you have cooked.
# Shopping lists are throwaway; ignore them by uncommenting the next line.
# shopping-lists/

